des:
The Gynoid Home skill allows you to control your Gynoid Smart Home products via Amazon’s Alexa.

To use this skill you need to have: 
- The Gynoid Home application installed on your smartphone (download available on AppStore for iOS and Google Play for Android OS); 
- A Gynoid Home account created via the Gynoid Home application; 
- Purchased Gynoid’s smart home products such as the SmartCube or SmartPlugs or others; 
- An Amazon account through Amazon App Store or Amazon official website and install the Amazon’s Alexa app from the Amazon App Store;
- Purchased Amazon’s echo.

When you enable this skill, you will be prompted to link your echo to your Gynoid Home account. You will have to provide your Gynoid Home username and password. Once you log in and the authorization is successful, the Alexa Echo can control your devices.

Here’s the complete capability list:

Turn on/off the device name.

Note: the ‘Device name’ is the name of the device in the device list of your Gynoid Home App. You need to add all the devices to your Gynoid Home app. Each device must have a unique name, where each name can only be composed of one to three words, and cannot contain numbers nor special characters.
